    "created_at": "2013-08-26T05:16:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-08-26T05:16:38Z",
    "body": "@huonw That won't work for me, though. The real macro that hit this needs `$code` to see a variable that in one arm is `&[u8]` and in the other is `~[u8]`. The real macro is closer to\n\n```\nmacro_rules! foo(\n    ($var:ident, $code:expr) => (\n        if test($var) {\n            let var = cond.raise($var.to_owned());\n            $code\n        } else {\n            $code\n        }\n    )\n)\n```\n",
